540  uint32 timedCriteriaStartType; // 27 m_timer_start_event Only appears with timed achievements, seems to be the type of starting a timed Achievement, only type 1 and some of type 6 need manual starting: 1: ByEventId(?) (serverside IDs), 2: ByQuestId, 5: ByCastSpellId(?), 6: BySpellIdTarget(some of these are unknown spells, some not, some maybe spells), 7: ByKillNpcId, 9: ByUseItemId

547  {
548  if (!timeLimit)
549  return false;
550 
551  // in case raw.value == timedCriteriaMiscId in timedCriteriaMiscId stored spellid/itemids for cast/use, so repeating aura start at first cast/use until fails
552  return requiredType == ACHIEVEMENT_CRITERIA_TYPE_COMPLETE_QUEST || raw.value != timedCriteriaMiscId;

987  int GetIndexFitTo(uint32 raceMask, uint32 classMask) const
988  {
989  for (int i = 0; i < 4; ++i)
990  {
991  if ((BaseRepRaceMask[i] == 0 || (BaseRepRaceMask[i] & raceMask)) &&

1013 struct FactionTemplateEntry
1014 {
1015  uint32 ID; // 0 m_ID
1016  uint32 faction; // 1 m_faction
1017  uint32 factionFlags; // 2 m_flags
1018  uint32 factionGroupMask; // 3 m_factionGroup
1019  uint32 friendGroupMask; // 4 m_friendGroup
1020  uint32 enemyGroupMask; // 5 m_enemyGroup
1021  uint32 enemyFaction[4]; // 6 m_enemies[4]
1022  uint32 friendFaction[4]; // 10 m_friend[4]
1023  //------------------------------------------------------- end structure
1024 
1025  // helpers
1026  bool IsFriendlyTo(FactionTemplateEntry const& entry) const
1027  {
1028  if (entry.faction)
1029  {
1030  for (unsigned int i : enemyFaction)
1031  if (i == entry.faction)
1032  return false;
1033  for (unsigned int i : friendFaction)
1034  if (i == entry.faction)
1035  return true;
1036  }
1037  return (friendGroupMask & entry.factionGroupMask) || (factionGroupMask & entry.friendGroupMask);
1038  }
1039  bool IsHostileTo(FactionTemplateEntry const& entry) const
1040  {
1041  if (entry.faction)
1042  {
1043  for (unsigned int i : enemyFaction)
1044  if (i == entry.faction)
1045  return true;
1046  for (unsigned int i : friendFaction)
1047  if (i == entry.faction)
1048  return false;
1049  }
1050  return (enemyGroupMask & entry.factionGroupMask) != 0;
1051  }
1052  bool IsHostileToPlayers() const { return (enemyGroupMask & FACTION_GROUP_MASK_PLAYER) != 0; }
1053  bool IsNeutralToAll() const
1054  {
1055  for (unsigned int i : enemyFaction)
1056  if (i != 0)
1057  return false;
1058  return enemyGroupMask == 0 && friendGroupMask == 0;
1059  }
1060  bool IsContestedGuardFaction() const { return (factionFlags & FACTION_TEMPLATE_FLAG_ATTACK_PVP_ACTIVE_PLAYERS) != 0; }
1061 };

1630  uint32 getssdMultiplier(uint32 mask) const
1631  {
1632  if (mask & 0x4001F)
1633  {
1634  if (mask & 0x00000001) return ssdMultiplier[0];
1635  if (mask & 0x00000002) return ssdMultiplier[1];
1636  if (mask & 0x00000004) return ssdMultiplier[2];
1637  if (mask & 0x00000008) return ssdMultiplier2;
1638  if (mask & 0x00000010) return ssdMultiplier[3];
1639  if (mask & 0x00040000) return ssdMultiplier3;
1640  }
1641  return 0;
1642  }

1650  if (mask & 0x00000080) return armorMod[2];
1651  if (mask & 0x00000100) return armorMod[3];

1655  if (mask & 0x00400000) return armorMod2[2]; // mail
1656  if (mask & 0x00800000) return armorMod2[3]; // plate

1767 struct ClassFamilyMask
1768 {

1770  uint32 Flags2;
1771 
1772  ClassFamilyMask() : Flags(0), Flags2(0) {}
1773  explicit ClassFamilyMask(uint64 familyFlags, uint32 familyFlags2 = 0) : Flags(familyFlags), Flags2(familyFlags2) {}
1774 
1775  bool Empty() const { return Flags == 0 && Flags2 == 0; }
1776  bool operator!() const { return Empty(); }
1777  operator void const* () const { return Empty() ? nullptr : this; }// for allow normal use in if(mask)
1778 
1779  bool IsFitToFamilyMask(uint64 familyFlags, uint32 familyFlags2 = 0) const
1780  {
1781  return (Flags & familyFlags) || (Flags2 & familyFlags2);
1782  }
1783 
1784  bool IsFitToFamilyMask(uint32 index, uint32 familyFlags) const
1785  {
1786  if (index == 0)
1787  return Flags & familyFlags;
1788  else if (index == 1)
1789  return Flags & (uint64(familyFlags) << 32);
1790  else
1791  return Flags2 & familyFlags;
1792  }
1793 
1794  bool IsFitToFamilyMask(ClassFamilyMask const& mask) const
1795  {
1796  return (Flags & mask.Flags) || (Flags2 & mask.Flags2);
1797  }
1798 
1799  uint64 operator& (uint64 mask) const // possible will removed at finish convertion code use IsFitToFamilyMask
1800  {
1801  return Flags & mask;
1802  }
1803 
1804  ClassFamilyMask& operator|= (ClassFamilyMask const& mask)
1805  {
1806  Flags |= mask.Flags;
1807  Flags2 |= mask.Flags2;
1808  return *this;
1809  }
1810 };

1969  uint32 GetAllEffectsMechanicMask() const
1970  {
1971  uint32 mask = 0;
1972  if (Mechanic)
1973  mask |= 1 << Mechanic;
1974  for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_EFFECT_INDEX; ++i)
1975  if (Effect[i] && EffectMechanic[i])
1976  mask |= 1 << EffectMechanic[i];
1977  return mask;
1978  }
